# Cyrius — Language Reference (Index)
# How to read, write, and reason about Cyrius programs.
# Replaces the monolithic content/cyrius/language.cyml (4144 lines, 73 entries)
# split during vidya v2.4.3 into 6 surface-area files.
#
# Compiler-internal patches, bug-pin retrospectives, and release-arc
# narrative were moved to content/cyrius/field_notes/compiler/ for later
# review and cleanup. Resolved patches were dropped — the fix is in the
# compiler now and no agent action is needed.
#
# Verified on Cyrius 6.1.18 (current as of 2026-06-09). The v6.0.0
# cycle opened 2026-05-19 with the two-binary rename ceremony: cyrc → cybs
# (Cyrius Bootstrap) + cc5 → cycc (Cyrius Computer Compiler).
# Bootstrap chain is now seed (asm) → cybs → cycc. v5.x closed
# at v5.11.69 after 70 slots over 11 days — longest minor in
# Cyrius history. v6.0.x closed at v6.0.91 (91 patches: rename
# ceremony + native TLS 1.2/1.3 + the CYRIUS_TARGET_AGNOS userspace
# target + the macOS/Windows cross-OS reckoning — see
# retros/v60x.cyml). mabda 3.0 fold was DROPPED from v5.11.x at
# .67-.68 boundary; folded into stdlib at 3.0.1 in v6.0.x. cycc
# self-host byte-identical at 1,045,120 B (~1.05 MB, v6.1.18; was
# 931,072 B at v6.0.87 and 874,240 B at the v6.0.0 cut — the v6.1.x
# growth is the TS frontend + JS emitter + the 64 KB TS parse
# scratch + the Windows-pillar work). Stdlib module count: 94 (85
# stdlib + 9 vendored deps). cycc_aarch64 594,848 B / cycc_win
# 814,592 B cross-builds.
#
# v6.1.x ("Backend Codegen Multi-Arc") shipped through .18: PIE
# position-independent codegen on x86_64 (.6) + aarch64 (.8) via
# --pie/CYRIUS_PIE=1; the .gnu.hash dynamic-link migration (.9);
# Phase D — the TS/TSX → JS emitter `cycc --emit-js` (.11, on the
# AST allocator fix .10) + `cyrius build --target=js` (.12); and the
# Windows-pillar pack (.16-.18): PE var-syscall runtime dispatch +
# `lib/sync.cyr` portable mutex (.16), `nanosleep(35)`→Sleep (.17),
# and the Windows directory-listing port — `dir_list`/`is_dir`/
# `dir_walk` via FindFirstFileW + `lib/fs_win.cyr` (.18). See
# retros/v61x.cyml.
# api-surface continues to grow with per-cycle additions —
# v5.11.x added the per-repo isolation surface (cyrius.cyml
# [package].cyrius field + version-resolved CLI dispatch), the
# parser-to-emit named-op refactor with drift-gate, ELF64
# kernel emit + multiboot2 + EFI64-entry tag, the UEFI
# Application PE emit arc (gnoboot MVP unblocker), the
# byte-array literal syntax (.51), `fn efi_main(handle, st)`
# entry convention (.52), the cycc-side cyml pin-drift check
# (.57), the wrapper `lib sync` / `--strict-pin` / `--version`
# manifest-pin enhancements (.58), the DCE-aware undef-fn
# reachability filter cross-arch (.59), agnos gvar-init-order
# static-init tables (.64), the two-binary rename ceremony at
# v6.0.0 (cyrc → cybs + cc5 → cycc; back-compat symlinks for
# the v6.0.x window), CVE-05 tok_names mangle-path guard
# (.65), bridge-compiler retirement (.66; chain shortened to
# seed → cyrc → cc5), build-cc5-verify.sh fixpoint verifier
# script (.67), and the heap-map full reorganization (.68; brk
# 86.6 → 77.6 MB). See retros/v511x.cyml for the cycle
# narrative including the v5.x_cycle_close summary.
#
# v5.11.x highlights (in-flight, 59 slots through 2026-05-17):
# - IRON-BOOT PAPERCUT 4-SLOT ARC (.56-.59): filing
#   2026-05-16 with 4 items (LSP false-positive flood,
#   undef-fn "will crash" wording, wrapper/manifest pin drift,
#   shadow-lib note over-fires). Closed cleanly across the
#   absorber band per user split-by-surface direction. .56:
#   LSP forks `cyrius check --with-deps` wrapper (was: raw
#   cycc, NULL envp, no [deps.*] resolution); undef-fn
#   `(will crash at runtime)` → `(call site may be
#   unreachable)` cross-arch. .57: cycc `_check_cyml_pin_drift`
#   surfaces toolchain drift via env-tunable
#   `CYRIUS_NO_WARN_PIN_DRIFT` / `CYRIUS_STRICT_PIN`;
#   shadow-lib note rewritten as content-compare (was:
#   directory-existence). .58: wrapper polish (`cyrius lib
#   sync`, `--strict-pin` flag, `--version` manifest-pin line)
#   + `scripts/version-bump.sh` rebuild fix for the wrapper
#   that had been stuck embedding .25 since 2026-05-12. .59:
#   DCE-aware reachability filter cross-arch — aarch64 gained
#   full DCE bitmap pass (mirrors x86 since v5.10.x) so
#   `vec_get`-from-dead-`vec_find` style refs stay silent.
# - BYTE-ARRAY LITERAL + EFI_MAIN CONVENTION (.51-.53):
#   `var foo[N] = { 0x.., ... };` literal feeds gnoboot's EFI
#   GUIDs + UTF-16LE strings. `fn efi_main(handle, st)`
#   convention auto-trampolines firmware args. v5.11.53
#   hotfix for MR-form `mov r/m64, r64` REX prefix typo
#   (`0x4C → 0x49`) — gotcha worth remembering: MR-form puts
#   dst in r/m field, src in reg field; REX.B (not REX.R)
#   extends the dst.
# - UEFI APPLICATION PE EMIT ARC (.47-.49): 3-slot arc
#   unblocking the AGNOS sovereign UEFI bootloader gnoboot
#   (~2000 LoC of cyrius replacing GRUB on the boot path).
#   `_TARGET_EFI_APPLICATION` flag + `CYRIUS_TARGET_EFI=1`
#   env var. Subsystem 3 → 10 (EFI_APPLICATION). EEXIT emits
#   single 0xC3 (ret) under EFI mode — firmware reads rax as
#   EFI_STATUS. ExitProcess import skipped; Data Dirs [1]/[12]
#   zeroed; NX_COMPAT forced; RELOCS_STRIPPED cleared (latter
#   was the v5.11.49 OVMF runtime smoke discovery — UEFI
#   firmware treats the bit as exact-ImageBase-or-fail).
#   `_pe_register_kernel32` 9-fn refactor squeeze-in at .47.
#   New `programs/efi_probe.cyr` (.48) boots end-to-end under
#   qemu+OVMF (.49 runtime smoke gate green).
# - ELF64 KERNEL EMIT + AGREEMENT FIX (.43-.46): EMITELF64_KERNEL
#   for AGNOS UEFI x86_64 boot (Path A). v5.11.46 fixed FIXUP↔
#   EMITELF64_KERNEL entry-arithmetic mismatch (`kmode==1`
#   branch hardcoded 0x100060 ELF32+mb1 layout vs the new ELF64+
#   mb2 0x1000A8). Path A subsequently dead-on-iron due to GRUB
#   `grub_relocator64_efi_boot` W^X bug under modern UEFI;
#   replaced by Path C (gnoboot, .47-.49).
# - PARSER-TO-EMIT NAMED-OP REFACTOR + DRIFT GATE (.35-.39):
#   per-backend EMIT_<OP> helpers replace direct `EB(S, 0xXX)`
#   byte emits in `parse_*.cyr`. Classes B (PIC-vs-direct
#   address loads), C (f64 unary ops), D (v5.7.12 audit doc).
#   v5.11.39 drift gate scans for any remaining EB(S,...) and
#   fails check.sh. Structurally locks the refactor.
# - ELF SECTION-HEADER PARITY SWEEP (.29-.34): kernel + user-bin
#   ELF emitters across all 5 instantiations (x86 user/kernel,
#   aarch64 user/kernel, cyrld linker) brought to section-header
#   parity for GRUB compatibility + tooling acceptance.
# - PER-REPO ISOLATION ARC (.17 + .25 + .26): three-part close
#   on the snapshot-ping-pong wipe vector. (.17) `cbt/deps.cyr`
#   stdlib_dir resolution rewritten: dev-mode-first (./lib when
#   src/main.cyr exists) → cyrius.cyml-pinned snapshot → legacy
#   global fallback. (.25) `cyrius` CLI now reads cyrius.cyml
#   `[package].cyrius` field and re-execs to the matching
#   `~/.cyrius/versions/<pin>/bin/cyrius` with CYRIUS_RESOLVED=1
#   loop guard. (.26) `cyriusly use 5.11.X` defaults to writing
#   cyrius.cyml's pin instead of `~/.cyrius/current`; `--global`
#   keeps the legacy global-pointer write. Sibling agents
#   flipping global state no longer affect other repos.
# - STDLIB ANNOTATION ARC (.1-.7): seven phases of return-type
#   annotations across native lib/ + per-arch syscall peers +
#   compiler internals.
# - 9-SIBLING FOLDIN CASCADE (.5): single-slot fold of vani /
#   patra / agnosys / sandhi / sakshi / sigil / yukti / sankoch /
#   niyama via the sandhi pattern; retired .cyrius-toolchain in
#   favor of cyrius.cyml [package].cyrius as the single version-
#   pin source of truth.
# - P(-1) HARDENING SWEEP (.45): 4-item bundle including
#   `_cc5_contamination_gate` (greps build/cc5 for mabda/wgpu
#   strings — the v5.11.43-style slip signature), `cyrius vet`
#   restored as real audit tool, dead-fn report gated behind
#   `CYRIUS_DCE_VERBOSE=1`, state.md compression 1451→583 lines.
# - LSP SEMANTIC TOKENS LOCALS+PARAMS (.42): textDocument/
#   semanticTokens/full now colors locals + parameters distinctly
#   from globals/fn-names/types. cyrius-lsp argv[0] self-resolution
#   (.44) via /proc/self/exe lets editors with minimal-env LSP
#   launchers find cycc without $CYRIUS_HOME / $HOME.
# - CVE-08 HARDENING + f64_abs PEEPHOLE (.40-.41): cld (0xFC)
#   emitted before any rep movsb/stosb to clear direction flag;
#   f64_abs(x) peephole replaces 6-instr sequence with 2-instr
#   ANDPS + RET.
#
# Additional v5.11.x highlights (front + middle, .1-.34):
# - STDLIB ANNOTATION ARC (.1-.7): seven phases of return-type
#   annotations across native lib/ + per-arch syscall peers +
#   compiler internals.
# - 9-SIBLING FOLDIN CASCADE (.5): single-slot fold of vani /
#   patra / agnosys / sandhi / sakshi / sigil / yukti / sankoch /
#   niyama via the sandhi pattern; retired .cyrius-toolchain in
#   favor of cyrius.cyml [package].cyrius as the single version-
#   pin source of truth.
# - PER-REPO ISOLATION ARC (.17 + .25 + .26): three-part close
#   on the snapshot-ping-pong wipe vector via cyrius.cyml
#   [package].cyrius + version-resolved CLI dispatch +
#   `cyriusly use --global` opt-in for legacy global writes.
# - PE/WIN64 PATH-API SURFACE (.21-.23): syscall 83/87/89 auto-
#   import + CreateDirectoryW/DeleteFileW dispatch (.21); UTF-16
#   widening fix on Win11 26200 (.23); PE-mode programs/check.cyr
#   gate exercising CreateFileW + CreateDirectoryW on cass.
# - AARCH64-NATIVE BUILD REPAIR (.27): two stacked stale-fork
#   bugs latent since the v5.5.16 main_*.cyr per-arch split.
#   pi-side CI smoke at v5.11.37 closes the gate-gap class.
# - PARSER NESTED-CALL DIAGNOSTIC (.28): bote 2.7.1 nested-call
#   `expected ')', got string` closed no-repro; hint line in
#   ERR_EXPECT gestures at "stage inner call into `var`". Root
#   cause likely silently closed by v5.11.18 identifier buffer
#   doubling — see docs/development/issues/2026-05-13-bote-nested-call-state-leak-root-cause.md
#   for cold-case investigation pin.
# - SLOT-MAP CONSOLIDATION AS REAL ACTIVITY (.16, .27): when
#   arc collapse or mid-slot re-scope frees runway, shift
#   pinned items forward and grow the OPEN buffer band at the
#   back. Buffer band moves, pin order doesn't.
#
# Prior v5.10.x highlights (closed 2026-05-10):
# - REAL TYPE SYSTEM arc (v5.10.1-.26): 5-phase. Type
#   annotations parsed + stored in registry, call-site
#   arg-type checking, overload dispatch on param-type
#   fingerprint, return-type recording, sum-type
#   rewriting. Unblock for typed-simd value-form params.
# - Typed-simd value-type ABI arc (v5.10.28-.39): 11 phases.
#   f64v2 + f64v4 as primitive value types; XMM/V register
#   pair param + return ABI on SysV / AAPCS; retptr-style
#   on Win64 PE; cx 4-register pair-quad. Pointer-form is
#   universal; value-form gated by CYRIUS_HAS_VAL_SIMD_PARAMS
#   (predefined in non-PE main_*.cyr). Pointer-vs-value
#   overload dispatch at v5.10.39 routes `f64v2_add(&x, &y)`
#   to `f64v2_add_ptr` transparently.
# - TLS surface completion (v5.10.13 + v5.10.21 + v5.10.34):
#   the full 10-fn surface lib/tls.cyr filed by mabda landed;
#   v5.10.34 added early-data status (TLS_EARLY_DATA_NOT_SENT
#   / REJECTED / ACCEPTED), tls_get_early_data_status,
#   tls_session_get_max_early_data.
# - sandhi 1.3.3 fold (v5.10.34): 1.1.0 → 1.3.3 (+1,194 lines)
#   matching the sandhi-pattern foldin lifecycle.
# - 3 locname-staleness surfacings: ptyp 89-91 missed in
#   v5.10.35's PARSE_SIMD_EXT fix; surfaced at v5.10.39
#   when value-form lib/simd.cyr siblings made the stale-
#   collision reliable. Same root cause as ptyp 93-130.
#   New gotcha entry covers the duplicate-dispatch audit
#   pattern.
# - install.sh `cp -L` same-file collision discovery
#   (v5.10.37): `cyrius deps` symlinks + snapshot symlinks
#   to same inode → cp -L fails → set -e exits before
#   ~/.cyrius/bin symlink-update block. Multi-bump streak
#   produced false-stale `cyrius-prompt-info`. Workaround
#   manual; fix pinned for v5.10.46 closeout (Option C
#   architectural: cyrius deps physical-copy).
#
# Prior v5.9.x highlights — closed at v5.9.43 (2026-05-08; 43
